                                              Cloud Computing Fundamentals
                                              
1 - Why Cloud Computing ---- In Early 2000 when you start a Business and In business if the used of cloud computing then you have to need set up infrastructure , you have also
need of man power for Mangement . In those days very few people know about Cloud Computing . Those have cloud computing of knowledge who have havily charged for his services .
Just think about it how difficult is start the bussiness.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2-  Challanges ------(a) - Invest Heavily for Setup.
(b) - Invest in Resources .
(c) - Scalability
(d) - Less time to focus on Business .
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3 - How Cloud Computing Helps ? ---- (a) - Cloud Computing is Analogous to Electricity Supply .
(b) - You Pay What You Use .
(c) - Somebody Else Mangages the services .
(d) - Focus on Your bussiness .
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4 - What is Cloud Computing ? ----- In Simple words Cloud Computing enables on demond services like compute , storage , Networking etc. Which can be accessed through the
internet and the user is not required to manages these resources . These can be access through the Internet from anywhere across the Globel .
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5 - Features ----------- (a) - Pay as you Go 
(b) - Scalable
(c) - Flexible
(d) - Secure and Disaster .
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6 - Cloud Service Model Types ---There are three main service models of cloud computing .
1 - Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS)
2 - Platform as a Service (PaaS) 
3 - Software as a Service (SaaS).
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7 - IaaS (Infrastructure as Service) -----Hardware, software and your application code has to be managed. You select the servers to activate (either physical or virtual), 
install the OS and software stack, then finally deploy your applications. Some providers offer very low-level controls so that you can build your own data center in the cloud.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8 - PaaS (Platform-as-a-Service)---------This type of service abstracts away all of the hardware decisions. Only the software stack and your application code has to be managed.
Select the appropriate provider depending on the software stack you want then deploy your applications. The actual servers, network and storage are all taken care of
automatically by the platform.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
9 - SaaS (Software as a Service)--------This is the highest abstraction level and means you are just using a web application and never see the hardware and software stack that
makes it run. You enter your own data into the application provided however some of the bigger applications allow for building custom apps on top (e.g. Facebook).
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
10 - Cloud Deployment Models ----  (a) - Public
(b) - Private
(c) - Hybrid
(d) - Community
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
11 - Cloud Computing Myths ----- (a) - Cloud Computing Cuts Jobs . 
(b) - Cloud is for Techies Alone .
(c) - Cloud Computing is not safe . Cloud is Just for Virtualization .
(d) - Cloud is Just for Virtualization .
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
12 - Popular Cloud Service Providers --- (a) - Amazon  Web Services . 
(b) - Google Cloud Platform . 
(c) - Microsoft Azure . 
(d) - IBM Cloud .


